---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import NavbarPages from "../components/NavbarPages";
import SmallButton from "../components/SmallButton";
---

<Layout title='MaDrPortfolio | MaDr'>
	<NavbarPages client:only='react' />
	<div class='w-full overflow-hidden'>
		<div class='w-screen h-[50vh] relative'>
			<div class='absolute top-0 left-0 w-full h-[50vh] z-5 bg-black/60'></div>
			<img
				class='absolute z-[-500]'
				src='https://raw.githubusercontent.com/MaDrCloudDev/projectsImages/master/madrportfolio.webp'
				alt='/'
			/>
			<div
				class='absolute text-3xl font-bold top-[70%] max-w-[1240px] w-full left-[50%] right-[50%] translate-x-[-50%] translate-y-[-50%] text-white p-2'>
				<h2 class='py-2 text-yellow-400'>MaDrPortfolio</h2>
				<h3>Astro / React / Tailwind</h3>
			</div>
		</div>
		<div class='mx-auto p-10 grid md:grid-cols-5 gap-8 pt-8 bg-black'>
			<div class='col-span-4'>
				<p class='text-xl font-bold text-yellow-400 mb-4'>Description</p>
				<p class='mb-4'>
					My modern visual portfolio built with Astro, React components, &
					Tailwind
				</p>
				<h2 class='text-lg text-blue-600 mb-4'>Overview</h2>
				<p class='mb-4'>
					I originally built this portfolio in Next.js to get a better handle on
					Next 13 as I move towards developing more apps in Vercel's ecosystem.
					You can view that version here:{" "}
					<a href='https://nextjsportfolio.madr.io/'>
						<span class='text-yellow-400'>Next.js version</span>.
					</a>{" "}
					While experiencing no problems in production or hosting the app on Vercel,
					I ran into too many incompatibilities with Next Image components and hosting
					Next 13 on Cloudflare.
				</p>
				<p class='mb-4'>
					Since the site is static anyways, I decided to spend a day rewriting
					the app in Astro. I cleaned up the the UI a bit, added Tailwind's
					HeadlessUI, and pieced together a much cleaner, much faster version of
					my new portfolio. It's still a work in progress.
				</p>
				<p>
					In time, I plan to migrate the JSX pages to Astro pages, leaving only
					the actual components as JSX. Some unique challenges I encountered
					included: How to implement icons with on-hover effects in without
					access to React/Icons, and how to conditionally change CSS based on
					route without access to useEffect on Next/Router. I ended up using
					inline SVGs with on-hover fill changes for the icons, and I simply
					created a second Navbar component for my pages instead of changing CSS
					based on route.
				</p>
				<a
					href='https://madr.io/'
					target='_blank'>
					<SmallButton text='Demo' />
				</a>
			</div>
			<div
				class='col-span-4 md:col-span-1 shadow-lg shadow-gray-700 rounded-xl p-4'>
				<div class='p-2'>
					<p class='text-center font-bold pb-2 text-yellow-400'>Technologies</p>
					<div class='grid grid-cols-3 md:grid-cols-1'>
						<p class='text-gray-200 py-2 flex items-center'>
							<bullet class='text-4xl mr-2 text-blue-600'>&bull;</bullet>
							Astro
						</p>
						<p class='text-gray-200 py-2 flex items-center'>
							<bullet class='text-4xl mr-2 text-blue-600'>&bull;</bullet>
							React
						</p>
						<p class='text-gray-200 py-2 flex items-center'>
							<bullet class='text-4xl mr-2 text-blue-600'>&bull;</bullet>
							Tailwind
						</p>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
			<a href='/#projects'>
				<p class='text-xl font-bold underline cursor-pointer text-yellow-400'>
					‚Üê Back
				</p>
			</a>
		</div>
	</div>
</Layout>
